## ROOT CAUSE (diagnosed, reproducible)

The teacher-forced ablation is a PER-EPISODE SELF-DEPENDENCY oracle, NOT a per-query relevance gate.
For each candidate it teacher-forces THAT candidate's OWN ep.secret and ablates THAT candidate's OWN
source rows -> every novel needle self-collapses catastrophically (-24..-50) REGARDLESS of the live
query, because deleting a needle's source rows always strands its own teacher-forced secret. The live
query is in the cache but barely modulates the score (the secret, not the query, drives the decode).
So argmin_j collapse_j picks the episode with the globally steepest self-collapse (the most code-dense
secret, ep_n_div_034) for EVERY query, matched or foreign. The absolute TAU=-8 gate cannot discriminate:
the true needle, a wrong needle, and a foreign-driven pick all clear -8 by ~25-40 nats.

This is exactly the offline-labeler property (each ep self-tests with its own secret -> all collapse),
which is a sound ADMISSION oracle (is this episode internally load-bearing?) but NOT a RECALL relevance
signal (which episode does THIS query want?). Promoting it per-candidate over a shared live query does not
introduce query-conditioning; the collapse remains query-independent. Confirmed by the matrix: across all
10 matched queries the per-episode collapse vector is near-constant; the argmin is the same fixed episode.

## WHAT THE LEARNED W_c HEAD HAS THAT THIS GATE LACKS

The deployed SP_B3_WC head (G-CHAT-B3-WC-DIV2: 360/361 recall + 50/50 reject) scores relevance from the
LIVE query-Q against each episode-K (logsumexp-mean) -> the score IS query-conditioned, so the argmax
tracks the query. The ablation gate's collapse is NOT query-conditioned, so its argmin does not. The
ablation oracle's correct role is the LABELER (it minted the div corpus labels) + a future ADMISSION gate
on novel live episodes, NOT the live recall selector. The live selector remains the learned W_c head.

## DELTA / SAFETY

- routes.rs SP_INT2 branch extended (Step 3): bounded-N (last-W of registry u nightshift with resolvable
  ep.secret+ep.tok; live-no-sidecar episodes SKIPPED, logged as the Phase-B extension), per-candidate
  teacher-forced ablation reusing the SP_B3_DISPOSER=2 FFI sequence EXACTLY, argmin-collapse absolute gate
  vs SP_INT2_TAU. ACCEPT -> one kv::replay into the live cache; NULL -> nothing (anchor-pristine).
- Rewind-pristine HELD: per-candidate debug_assert(position==anchor) after each probe; net dpos delta 0;
  Jmax=64 assert per candidate (npos+ng ~28-35 <= 64, no skips: probed=91 skipped=0 every turn).
- int2_decided guard: when SP_INT2 renders a verdict, SP_B3_WC / SP_B3_DISPOSER / q.K fire branches are
  skipped (no double-fire). SP_B3_WC + the offline disposer remain intact and default-off-equivalent.
- Default-off (SP_INT2 unset) = byte-identical null floor (no new code path entered).

